\f1\b \cf0 3. \ul Recommended Further Monitoring
\f0\b0 \ulnone \
Regular, comprehensive audits should be conducted to compare predicted scores across racial and age groups. Especially review the individuals predicted to be in the high-risk category for potential patterns of bias. Monitor for drift in the importance of the features over time, and periodically retrain the model with updated (or more evenly-balanced) data. Also monitor for the instability when SHAP and LIME result in very different explanations. \
High-impact cases, and borderline cases, should be reviewed by a human before any decisions are finalized or action steps are initiated. To facilitate this, clear documentation of the limitations of the model should be provided to users and decision makers, preferably in non-technical language, with regular opportunities for staff training. \
Most importantly, establish and publicize how an individual can view and contest or appeal their scores, including reviewing their personal data for accuracy.\
A committee should be formed and meet frequently to review the fairness, accountability, and policy alignment of the predicted scores, and adjudicate appeals.\
\
Thank you for your time and attention.}